{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/post/CodeSadbox","webpackCompilationHash":"43a07f76784e304bf1a0","result":{"data":{"blogPost":{"fields":{"authors":["Drake Costa"],"date":"2019-07-18T00:00:00.000Z","description":"In this week's release we've got the best new feature we hope you never have to use! But that's not all, we've got some other goodies to share too!","photo":"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/3144549?s=460&v=4","slug":"CodeSadbox","title":"CodeSadbox - Introducing improved Crash Reporting!"},"frontmatter":{"banner":{"publicURL":"/static/banner-d8c2bd197bc82f7e7a5d46685effc218.png"}},"html":"<p>Have you ever been using <a href=\"https://codesandbox.io\">CodeSandbox</a> only to encounter\na suddenly blank screen? We certainly have in development! Often, this occurs\nwhen one of our components encounters an error during render. For our part, we\ntry our best to weed out all of these cases before shipping new updates to you,\nbut occasionally these sorts of errors can and do pop up in rare edge cases in\nour production app.</p>\n<p>To make it more obvious that you've entered one of these states, we've\nimplemented a new <em>Error Boundary</em> component that will display a fallback UI\nwhich we're calling <em>CodeSadbox</em>:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 740px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ad0e11cd7a126571c439f41da982cd1f/84350/01_CodeSadbox.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.38225255972696%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"CodeSadbox\"\n        title=\"CodeSadbox\"\n        src=\"/static/ad0e11cd7a126571c439f41da982cd1f/bcf2d/01_CodeSadbox.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ad0e11cd7a126571c439f41da982cd1f/d5c4a/01_CodeSadbox.png 185w,\n/static/ad0e11cd7a126571c439f41da982cd1f/04e89/01_CodeSadbox.png 370w,\n/static/ad0e11cd7a126571c439f41da982cd1f/bcf2d/01_CodeSadbox.png 740w,\n/static/ad0e11cd7a126571c439f41da982cd1f/dbb75/01_CodeSadbox.png 1110w,\n/static/ad0e11cd7a126571c439f41da982cd1f/84350/01_CodeSadbox.png 1172w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>While we hope you'll never encounter this screen, in case you do, we've added a\nconvenient way for you to help let us know how you got there! By clicking on the\n<em>Report Crash</em> button, a new window will open that will take you directly to\n<a href=\"https://github.com\">GitHub</a> to file a new issue. Best of all, your new issue\nwill be pre-filled with some useful crash information!</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 740px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/0cc29749002cbcd55e28c94de9250942/ba6d6/02_Crash_Report.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 61.81818181818181%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Crash Report\"\n        title=\"Crash Report\"\n        src=\"/static/0cc29749002cbcd55e28c94de9250942/bcf2d/02_Crash_Report.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/0cc29749002cbcd55e28c94de9250942/d5c4a/02_Crash_Report.png 185w,\n/static/0cc29749002cbcd55e28c94de9250942/04e89/02_Crash_Report.png 370w,\n/static/0cc29749002cbcd55e28c94de9250942/bcf2d/02_Crash_Report.png 740w,\n/static/0cc29749002cbcd55e28c94de9250942/dbb75/02_Crash_Report.png 1110w,\n/static/0cc29749002cbcd55e28c94de9250942/ba6d6/02_Crash_Report.png 1155w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>In this initial version, the auto-generated crash report includes information\nabout your environment, the error message you encountered, and a component stack\ntrace. We plan to improve this over time to make it even easier to track down\nthose nasty bugs and get a fix issued asap!</p>\n<p>So if you're feeling up for a challenge, see if you can find your way to this\nelusive little box! We're excited to see what sort of bugs you can find!</p>\n<section>\n<h2 id=\"but-wait-theres-more\"><a href=\"#but-wait-theres-more\" aria-label=\"but wait theres more permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>But wait, there's more!</h2>\n<h4 id=\"custom-template-icons\"><a href=\"#custom-template-icons\" aria-label=\"custom template icons permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Custom Template icons</h4>\n<p>We've actually got a few other goodies to share this week! In our recent release\nof <a href=\"/post/Templates\">Templates</a>, you may have noticed that there was something\nmissing: the ability to add an icon to your new custom template. Well now we've\ngot a sweet new icon picker that you can access in your Template configuration\ninside of the <em>Project Info</em> panel:</p>\n<p><img src=\"/be6b40f635c220c563acc62db86df973/03_Template_Icons.gif\" alt=\"Custom Template icons\"></p>\n<h4 id=\"multiple-ports-in-containers\"><a href=\"#multiple-ports-in-containers\" aria-label=\"multiple ports in containers permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Multiple ports in Containers</h4>\n<p>Not only that, we've shipped a much requested feature for Containers: multiple\nport support! Now when your container begins listening on an additional port,\nyou'll see a toast notification in the bottom-right corner letting you know and\nproviding you the option to open a new browser preview tab as well:</p>\n<p><img src=\"/dfcde998ae0c78ede0b0051c988c7cb9/04_Multiple_Ports.gif\" alt=\"Multiple Ports\"></p>\n<p>With this update you'll be able to run both a web app and an API from a single\ncontainer instance with ease. We're excited about all the new projects this will\nenable!</p>\n<h4 id=\"prs-merged-bugs-fixed--code-refactored\"><a href=\"#prs-merged-bugs-fixed--code-refactored\" aria-label=\"prs merged bugs fixed  code refactored permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>PRs merged, bugs fixed &#x26; code refactored</h4>\n<p>Lastly, this week we've been focused on merging some outstanding PRs and fixing\nbugs. We're also in the process of re-writing the whole application in\n<a href=\"https://github.com/Microsoft/TypeScript\">TypeScript</a> and refactoring to use\n<a href=\"https://reactjs.org/docs/hooks-intro.html\">Hooks</a>. While not all of this work\nwill be immediately visible, these efforts are setting the foundation for\neverything that is to come!</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Thanks for using CodeSandbox and we look forward to sharing more updates with\nyou soon!</p>\n</section>"}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"id":"67dd0b4a-4a37-5f8d-b39a-73f5fd290e1c"}}}